OL,3,CGuernsey scraps International
OL,4,CBaccalaureate amid financial pressures
OL,6,FGuernsey's government has cancelled
OL,7,Fthe International Baccalaureate (IB)
OL,8,Fprogramme for new students, blaming
OL,9,Flow uptake and financial pressures.
OL,11,FThe post-16 qualification had already
OL,12,Fbeen paused for the current school
OL,13,Fyear, as only 14 students signed up.
OL,15,FThe two-year Diploma is seen as a way
OL,16,Ffor gifted pupils to demonstrate their
OL,17,Facademic prowess, with previous
OL,18,Fparticipants going on to secure
OL,19,Fscholarships and places at top
OL,20,Funiversities.
